We’re back, because my friends told me “get going on making a new core video, darn it!” 😂 And because I had a cute new shirt to show off 🤩
All you need is a water bottle as your weight. Let me know what you thought of the routine below! 
💪🏼
Special shout-out to @llbean for their pride month edition of their spf 50 sun shirt. Makes me so happy that they support EVERYONE! And I couldn’t be happier to wear it in support of my friends. ❤️ #LLBeanAmbassador #beanoutsider

Here’s the deal - every week in my bio I’ll be linking an article relating to climate change. Read the article, follow @protectourwinters and join their email list on protectourwinters.org to learn how you can get involved. Then get outside on a rad adventure and if you post about it, tag me - I want to see what you did!

To keep you inspired, each week I’ve got some really sick giveaways from @llbean, @oakleyskiing, @nuunhydration & @swixsportus. To be entered in each week’s giveaway, follow @protectourwinters, tag 3 friends in the comments below and tell me what you found most interesting about the week’s article! 
🤓
This first week’s article is by Kendra Pierre-Louis, “For a Climate Reporter, a dreaded question: ‘then why is it so cold?’” and your giveaway prize is a $100 gift certificate to @llbean AND a pair of @oakley Sutro Lite glasses. 😎
Winner will be randomly chosen and notified by DM, so check your messages! Each week will have a new article to read and a new winner, so have fun and keep crushing it!

node.text:
A lot of things in my life are - quite literally - a race. But not mental health! Let’s take a second to address a common misconception about how long recovery might take. 

Recovery from an eating disorder isn’t a race. There isn’t a universal “timeline” that you’re “supposed to follow”. 

Recovery is more like navigating a wild trail. 
🗺🧭
Not every step seems like it’s taking you forward - you might zig and zag and sometimes the trail even doubles back (darn it!) but every step can be celebrated because it took effort and heart to make it this far, and it’s taken you one step closer to your goal, even if you can’t see the finish yet. 

You might be tempted to take a side trail, and need to phone a friend to ask directions and stay on track. 

You might be someone who needs a trail guide to walk with you through the hard parts.

And on those hard parts, you may want a support crew! They can’t take these steps for you, but they CAN cheer you on and encourage you to keep going when you feel like giving up. 

You might encounter mud, rocks and roots that sometimes trip you up, and you learn how to scramble over them. 

Everyone’s trail looks different, and it will take different people different amounts of time to feel comfortable on the trail. 
Yet every step is absolutely worth taking! 
💛
Just a little reminder that if you’re working your way through your own trail towards recovery and mental health, it’s ok if your path is unique to you. 
🧡 Lucky and grateful to be here today as an #emilyprogramambassador @emilyprogram

You didn’t think I’d forget to give you a new core challenge for July, did you?!? 
Here it is:
1. Boat pose with right leg extended, left leg, then both legs
2. Leg lowers with weight held overhead - the farther back you hold it, the harder it gets!
3. Roll-ups that are slow and controlled, especially on the way down
4. Leg lowers at an angle to each side 

Start with body weight, working your way up to holding a plate over your head - and if you’re feeling crazy, use a slosh tube (like me in the video) for the extra challenge of weight that unpredictably moves! Try 30 seconds of each exercise. 💪🏼

Come train with us! ⚡️ While I’d love to be able to come run a workout with every team that reaches out, I can’t drive up and down the East coast all summer. But…you can come visit us in Stratton! We are opening up select workouts to anyone who wants to join us. All ages and abilities welcome! This is a great chance to ask questions, meet the team and do intervals with some of the best skiers in the world! It’s also free, so, you know, that’s kinda nice. 😉

Tomorrow at 8:30am (Saturday July 10th) meet us at the base of the Stratton Mountain Gondola for a ski walk interval session up the mountain! Bring shoes, water and short poles (if you have them)!

Next week on Wednesday July 14th, we are hosting an open skate roller ski clinic from 3-4pm in Stratton Sun Bowl. Come ski with us, do some drills and have fun with agility! 

Saturday July 17th at 9am we are doing a long run from the Mad Tom Notch parking lot for a loop around Griffith lake, Peru and Styles peaks. 
We will hang out at Hapgood pond for a swim and picnic lunch (bring your own) after! 
📷: Matt Whitcomb

IG vs reality…but in reverse? Swipe right to see what was happening just out of frame during Monday’s lift with Sports Illustrated. 👉🏼👀 Honestly, this was a great test of focus for me! This is a year of finding balance; of acknowledging pressure and expectations without being consumed by them. Of going all out because it’s what I love to do, not because of who’s watching, or who isn’t. That said…thank you @sifullframe for showing how we go all out and #liftlikeagirl 💪🏼
📷: @jcorkski
